#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:2
msgid "FunSearch Approach"
msgstr "FunSearch 方法"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:4
msgid ""
"FunSearch uses **LLM + evolutionary search** to automatically discover "
"heuristic algorithms for CVRP, without hand-crafting rules."
msgstr "FunSearch 使用 **LLM + 进化搜索** 自动发现 CVRP 启发式算法，无需人工设计规则。"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:8
msgid "Limitations of Classical Methods"
msgstr "传统方法的局限"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:10
msgid "Require hand-crafted heuristic rules"
msgstr "需要人工设计启发式规则"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:11
msgid "Poor generalisation across problem scales"
msgstr "泛化能力差，在不同规模问题上表现不稳定"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:12
msgid "Difficult to escape local optima"
msgstr "难以跳出局部最优"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:15
msgid "How FunSearch Works"
msgstr "FunSearch 的工作原理"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:17
msgid ""
"FunSearch treats algorithm discovery as a program synthesis problem. "
"Instead of tuning parameters, it evolves the *code itself*:"
msgstr "FunSearch 将算法发现视为程序合成问题。它不是调整参数，而是直接进化 *代码本身*："

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:20
#, fuzzy
msgid "**LLM generation**: sample candidate algorithm code from a prompt"
msgstr "**LLM 生成**：根据提示词生成候选算法代码"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:21
msgid "**Evaluation**: score candidates on benchmark instances"
msgstr "**评估筛选**：在数据集上评估候选算法性能"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:22
msgid ""
"**Evolutionary selection**: register high-scoring programs into the "
"database"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:23
msgid "**Iteration**: repeat until a high-quality algorithm emerges"
msgstr "**迭代改进**：多轮迭代后得到高质量算法"

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:25
msgid ""
"The key insight is that the LLM acts as a mutation operator — it reads "
"existing programs and writes improved versions, guided by the "
"evolutionary pressure of the programs database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:30
msgid "Specification Format"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:32
msgid ""
"A FunSearch run is driven by a *specification file* — a Python module "
"with two decorated functions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:47
msgid ""
"``@funsearch.evolve`` marks the function the LLM will rewrite each "
"iteration. The initial body serves as the seed program."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:49
msgid ""
"``@funsearch.run`` marks the evaluation harness. It receives a list of "
"test instances and must return a scalar score (higher = better)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:52
msgid ""
"The evaluator calls the ``evolve`` function internally; FunSearch only "
"replaces that one function while keeping the rest of the harness fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:56
msgid "Programs Database"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:58
msgid ""
"The programs database is the core data structure that drives the "
"evolutionary search. It maintains a diverse population of programs and "
"produces prompts for the LLM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:63
msgid "Islands"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:65
msgid ""
"The database is partitioned into **islands** (default: 10). Each island "
"evolves independently, which preserves diversity and prevents premature "
"convergence to a single local optimum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:69
msgid ""
"Every new program generated from a prompt on island *i* is registered "
"back into island *i*. Programs added at the very start (the seed) are "
"broadcast to all islands simultaneously."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:74
msgid "Clusters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:76
msgid ""
"Within each island, programs are grouped into **clusters** by their "
"*score signature* — a tuple of per-test scores across all evaluation "
"inputs:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:83
msgid ""
"Two programs land in the same cluster if and only if they produce "
"identical scores on every test input, meaning they are *behaviourally "
"equivalent* even if their code differs. Each cluster stores its "
"representative score (the score on the last test input) and all programs "
"that share that signature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:88
msgid ""
"When sampling a program from a cluster, shorter programs are preferred — "
"they are assigned higher probability via a softmax over negated lengths. "
"This acts as an implicit Occam's razor, favouring simpler "
"implementations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:93
msgid "Cluster Sampling and Temperature Schedule"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:95
msgid ""
"To build a prompt, the island samples ``functions_per_prompt`` clusters "
"(default: 3) using a **softmax over cluster scores**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:98
#, python-brace-format
msgid "P(\\text{cluster}_i) = \\text{softmax}\\!\\left(\\frac{s_i}{T}\\right)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:102
msgid ""
"where :math:`s_i` is the cluster's score and :math:`T` is the current "
"temperature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:105
msgid ""
"The temperature follows a **sawtooth schedule** that decreases within "
"each period and then resets:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:108
#, python-brace-format
msgid "T = T_0 \\times \\left(1 - \\frac{n \\bmod P}{P}\\right)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:112
msgid ""
"where :math:`T_0` is the initial temperature, :math:`n` is the total "
"number of programs registered so far, and :math:`P` is the period length."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:115
msgid ""
"**High temperature** (early in a period): near-uniform sampling → "
"exploration"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:116
msgid ""
"**Low temperature** (late in a period): peaked on best clusters → "
"exploitation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:118
msgid ""
"This oscillation prevents the search from locking onto a single cluster "
"too early while still exploiting good solutions as the period progresses."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:122
msgid "Island Reset"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:124
msgid ""
"Every ``reset_period`` seconds (default: 600 s), the **bottom half** of "
"islands (ranked by best score) are reset:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:127
msgid "The weak island is discarded and replaced with a fresh empty island."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:128
msgid "A random island from the surviving top half is chosen as the *founder*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:129
msgid "The founder's best program is seeded into the new island."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:131
msgid ""
"This mechanism eliminates stagnant sub-populations while preserving the "
"diversity of the surviving islands. The new island starts fresh but with "
"a strong seed, giving it a head start."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:136
msgid "Prompt Construction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:138
msgid ""
"When the LLM is asked to generate a new program, it receives a prompt "
"built from the sampled programs. The prompt is structured as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:141
msgid "The full specification template (imports, harness code, type definitions)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:142
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"The sampled programs, **sorted by score ascending** (worst first, best "
"last), renamed to ``_v0``, ``_v1``, …, ``_v{N-1}``. Each function after "
"``_v0`` gets a docstring ``\"Improved version of _v{i-1}.\"``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:145
#, python-brace-format
msgid ""
"An **empty function header** ``_v{N}`` with docstring ``\"Improved "
"version of _v{N-1}.\"``, which the LLM must complete."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:148
msgid "Example prompt structure:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:166
msgid ""
"Presenting programs in ascending score order gives the LLM a clear "
"improvement trajectory: it sees what was tried, how it improved, and is "
"asked to continue that trend."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:171
msgid "Sampler Loop"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:173
msgid ""
"One or more **samplers** run concurrently (or sequentially in the single-"
"process implementation). Each sampler:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:176
msgid "Calls ``database.get_prompt()`` to obtain a prompt and its ``island_id``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:177
msgid "Sends the prompt to the LLM and draws one or more code completions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:178
msgid "Parses each completion to extract the generated function body."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:179
msgid "Sends each parsed function to the **evaluator**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:181
msgid ""
"The sampler loop runs indefinitely until the configured number of "
"iterations or a time budget is exhausted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:185
msgid "Evaluator and Sandbox"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:187
msgid "The evaluator receives a generated function and:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:189
msgid "**Compiles** it — checks for syntax errors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:190
msgid ""
"**Runs** it inside a ``SimpleSandbox``: an isolated ``exec`` namespace "
"containing only ``math``, ``random``, and the problem-specific types. A "
"``SIGALRM`` timeout kills runs that exceed the per-call time limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:193
msgid ""
"**Scores** the function by calling the ``@funsearch.run`` harness on all "
"test inputs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:195
msgid ""
"**Registers** the scored function in the programs database under the "
"originating ``island_id``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/funsearch.rst:198
msgid ""
"Functions that raise exceptions, time out, or produce invalid solutions "
"receive a score of ``-inf`` and are discarded."
msgstr ""

